description.narrative:
The overall objective of the intervention is to develop an effective and sustainable framework for preventing and supressing money laundering and terrorist financing in Serbia. The overall objective is broken down into 7 outcomes, as follows:
Outcome 1: Strengthened compliance and oversight of AML/CFT financial and designated non-financial business and professions (DNFBPs);
Outcome 2: Enhanced Non-Profit Organizations (NPO) terrorist-financing risk management;
Outcome 3: Developed risk-based border controls related to cash and goods smuggling, terrorist financing, and proliferation;
Outcome 4: Increased transparency of beneficial ownership (BO) information for legal persons, arrangements and trusts;
Outcome 5: Enhanced criminal justice sector processing of ML/FT cases;
Outcome 6: Strengthened effectiveness in the confiscation of proceeds and instrumentalities of crime;
Outcome 7: Enhanced inter-agency cooperation on verification of asset declarations.
